    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-31T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-31T13:00:00-05:00" n="467"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">632.0023/11: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Porto Alegre</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Nasmith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Porto Alegre</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-31T15:00:00-03:00"
                            >October 31, 1930—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Entrance to port of Rio Grande which had been obstructed by the revolutionists
                    has now been officially reopened under compulsory pilotage. This information
                    should be of interest to American shipping interests New York, New Orleans and
                    Baltimore.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nasmith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
